# Cursor Rules

## Documentation and Code Standards

- All code must be well-documented with clear docstrings
- All comments and documentation must be in English (universal language)
- Use type hints for all function parameters and return values
- Follow Python PEP 8 style guidelines
- Include comprehensive error handling and logging

## Documentation Requirements

- Functions and classes must have docstrings following Google or NumPy style
- Inline comments should explain "why" not "what" (code should be self-explanatory)
- Complex logic must be documented with clear comments
- All public APIs must have complete type hints

## Code Quality

- Use descriptive variable names
- Keep functions focused and single-purpose
- Handle edge cases and errors gracefully
- Use appropriate logging levels (debug, info, warning, error)

## Language

- Code comments: English
- Docstrings: English
- Variable names: English
- Function names: English
- Error messages: English (for technical logs)
- User-facing strings: Can be localized as needed

